    class Assertions:
    """
    Description:
    	|  This Class provides methods which can be used to verify and assert the validations. The methods also allows reporting the PASS/FAIL results into Kibana.

    """

    def __init__(self):
        self.logger = LoggerClass().logger

    def kibana_insert_message_on_result(self, pbool_result, pstr_expected_message, pstr_actual_message=None, **kwargs):
        """
        Description:
        	|  This method is for internal usage and to insert into kibana based on the user inputs and it also has the provision to accept actual message in case of pass and actual message on fail

        :param pbool_result: pbool_result is the result that would come from a validation
        :type pbool_result: Boolean
        :param pstr_expected_message: pstr_expected_message  is the the kwarg parameter and it is the expected value of a this and this will be inserted in kibana
        :type pstr_expected_message: String
        :param pstr_actual_message: pstr_actual_message  is the the kwarg parameter and it is the actual value of a this and this will be inserted in kibana
        :type pstr_actual_message: String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_pass: pstr_actual_message_on_pass is the actual message when a validation is True
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_pass: String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_fail: pstr_actual_message_on_fail is the actual message when a validation is False
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_fail: String
        :param pobj_api_response: API Response Object
        :type pobj_api_response: Response
        :param pstr_error_code: pstr_error_code is the error category for assertion failure
        :type pstr_error_code: String

        :return: None


        .. warning::
        	|  this method is intended to be used internally and the end user is not advised to use this method.

        """
        try:
            str_actual_message_on_pass = kwargs.get("pstr_actual_message_on_pass")
            str_actual_message_on_fail = kwargs.get("pstr_actual_message_on_fail")
            pbool_execute_after_failure = kwargs.get("pbool_execute_after_failure", False)
            obj_api_response = kwargs.get('pobj_api_response', None)
            str_error_code = kwargs.get('pstr_error_code', CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_ZERO)
            if (str_actual_message_on_pass is not None and str_actual_message_on_fail is None) or (
                    str_actual_message_on_pass is None and str_actual_message_on_fail is not None):
                raise Exception(
                    "When 'pstr_actual_message_on_pass' would be passed 'pstr_actual_message_on_fail' should also be passed and vice-versa")
            elif str_actual_message_on_pass is None and str_actual_message_on_fail is None:
                if pstr_actual_message is None:
                    raise Exception(
                        "Neither the pstr_actual_message nor the 'pstr_actual_message_on_pass' and 'pstr_actual_message_on_fail' were passed")
                else:
                    str_actual_message_on_pass = str_actual_message_on_fail = pstr_actual_message
            elif str_actual_message_on_pass == str_actual_message_on_fail:
                raise Exception("pstr_actual_message_on_pass and pstr_actual_message_on_fail cannot be the same")

            if pbool_result:
                PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(pstr_expected_message, str_actual_message_on_pass, "Pass",
                                                      pobj_api_response=obj_api_response)
            else:
                PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(pstr_expected_message, str_actual_message_on_fail, "Fail",
                                                      pobj_api_response=obj_api_response,
                                                      pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure=pbool_execute_after_failure,
                                                      pstr_error=str_error_code)
        except Exception as e:
            PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(pstr_expected_message,
                                                  "Issue with parameters passed in assertion. Details:" + str(repr(e)),
                                                  "Fail")
            pytest.fail(str(e))

    class Web():

        error_utils = ErrorCategory()

        def __init__(self):
            self.assertions = Assertions()
            self.logger = self.assertions.logger

        def verify_element_is_visible(self, plocator, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
            """
            Description:
            	|  This method accepts a locator or web element and checks whether the element is visible on the page on not and based on the results returns True/False and also logs kibana results(optional)

            :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
            :type plocator: String/Web element
            :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
            :type bool_insert_kibana: Boolean
            :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
            :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
            :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
            :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String
            :param pstr_actual_message(kwargs): User can use it to overwrite default actual message
            :type pstr_actual_message(kwargs): String
            :param pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_pass kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is True
            :type pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): String
            :param pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_fail kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is False
            :type pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): String

            :return: Boolean
            """
            try:
                str_actual_message_on_pass = None
                str_actual_message_on_fail = None
                if 'explicit_wait' not in kwargs:
                    explicit_wait = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.default_explicit_wait
                else:
                    explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')
                bool_result = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.is_element_displayed(plocator, explicit_wait)

                if bool_insert_kibana:
                    str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                      "The given element/locator should be visible on the page")
                    str_actual_message = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message')
                    if str_actual_message is None:
                        str_actual_message_on_pass = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_pass',
                                                                "The given element/locator was visible.")
                        str_actual_message_on_fail = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_fail',
                                                                "The given element/locator was not visible.")

                    str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
                    self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                                    str_actual_message,
                                                                    pstr_actual_message_on_pass=str_actual_message_on_pass,
                                                                    pstr_actual_message_on_fail=str_actual_message_on_fail,
                                                                    pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                    pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                    return bool_result
                else:
                    return bool_result
            except Exception as e:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The given element/locator should be visible on the page")
                str_actual_message = "The given element/locator was not visible. The method threw an excepction. " + str(
                    e)
                str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
                self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message,
                                                                str_actual_message, pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                self.logger.exception(
                    "The given element/locator was not visible. The method threw an excepction. " + str(e))
                return False

        def verify_page_title(self, pstr_expected_title, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
            """
               Description:
                   |  This method is to check given title matches with current page title

               :param pstr_expected_title: pstr_expected_title is the expected title value
               :type pstr_expected_title: String
               :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
               :type bool_insert_kibana: Boolean
               :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
               :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String
               :param pstr_actual_message(kwargs): User can use it to overwrite default actual message
               :type pstr_actual_message(kwargs): String
               :param pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_pass kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is True
               :type pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): String
               :param pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_fail kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is False
               :type pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): String
               :return: Boolean
            """
            str_actual_message_on_pass = None
            str_actual_message_on_fail = None
            pstr_actual_page_title = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.get_title()
            bool_result = False
            try:
                if (pstr_actual_page_title == pstr_expected_title):
                    bool_result = True
                if bool_insert_kibana:
                    str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message', "The page title should be as expected")
                    str_actual_message = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message')
                    if str_actual_message is None:
                        str_actual_message_on_pass = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_pass',
                                                                "Page Title is as expected. Expected : " + pstr_expected_title + "Actual : " + pstr_actual_page_title)
                        str_actual_message_on_fail = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_pass',
                                                                "Page Title is as NOT as expected. Expected : " + pstr_expected_title + "Actual : " + pstr_actual_page_title)
                    str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
                    self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                                    str_actual_message,
                                                                    pstr_actual_message_on_pass=str_actual_message_on_pass,
                                                                    pstr_actual_message_on_fail=str_actual_message_on_fail,
                                                                    pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                    pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                return bool_result
            except Exception as e:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The Expected value : " + pstr_expected_title + "should be equal to Actual Value :" + pstr_actual_page_title)
                str_actual_message = "The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)
                str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
                self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message, str_actual_message,
                                                                pstr_error_code=str_error_code)

        def verify_text(self, plocator, expected_text_value, bool_insert_kibana=True, case_sensitive=False, **kwargs):
            """
            Description:
                |  This method accepts a locator or web element , fetches text from the web element ,
                |  compares it with the expected text value passed in parameters and based on the results returns True/False and
                |  also logs kibana results(optional) . The actual kibana result in this case is generated within the method.

            :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
            :type plocator: String/Web element
            :param expected_text_value: The expected text value of the web element
            :type expected_text_value: String
            :param case_sensitive: This parameter gives the option to user to compare the expected and actual text in a case sensitive manner
            :type case_sensitive: Boolean
            :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
            :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
            :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
            :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String

            :return: Boolean
            """
            actual_kibana_result = ""
            try:
                if 'explicit_wait' not in kwargs:
                    explicit_wait = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.default_explicit_wait
                else:
                    explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')
                bool_presence_result = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.is_element_present(plocator, explicit_wait)

                if bool_presence_result:
                    actual_text_value = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.get_web_element(plocator, explicit_wait).text
                    if case_sensitive:
                        bool_result = (expected_text_value == actual_text_value)
                        if bool_result:
                            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                        else:
                            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                                expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
                    else:
                        bool_result = (expected_text_value.lower() == actual_text_value.lower())
                        if bool_result:
                            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                        else:
                            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                                expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
                else:
                    bool_result = bool_presence_result
                    actual_kibana_result = "The given element was not found"

                if bool_insert_kibana:
                    str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                      "The expected and actual text should be equal")
                    str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
                    self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                                    actual_kibana_result,
                                                                    pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                    pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                    return bool_result
                else:
                    return bool_result
            except Exception as e:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The expected text value is " + expected_text_value)
                str_actual_message = actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)
                str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
                self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message, str_actual_message,
                                                                pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                return False

        def verify_attribute_value(self, plocator, attribute_name, expected_attribute_value, bool_insert_kibana=True,
                                   case_sensitive=False, **kwargs):
            """
            Description:
                |  This method accepts a locator or web element , fetches value of attribute name from the web element ,
                |  compares it with the expected attribute value passed in parameters and based on the results returns True/False and
                |  also logs kibana results

            :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
            :type plocator: String/Web element
            :param attribute_name: The attribute name for which the value needs to be fetched
            :type attribute_name: String
            :param expected_attribute_value: The expected attribute value of the web element
            :type expected_attribute_value: String
            :param case_sensitive: This parameter gives the option to user to compare the expected and actual text in a case sensitive manner
            :type case_sensitive: Boolean
            :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
            :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
            :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
            :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String

            :return: Boolean
            """

            try:
                if 'explicit_wait' not in kwargs:
                    explicit_wait = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.default_explicit_wait
                else:
                    explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')
                actual_attribute_value = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.get_attribute_value(plocator, attribute_name,
                                                                                            explicit_wait)

                if case_sensitive:
                    bool_result = (expected_attribute_value == actual_attribute_value)
                    if bool_result:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual attribute value are the same"
                    else:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual attribute value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                            expected_attribute_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_attribute_value)
                else:
                    bool_result = (expected_attribute_value.lower() == actual_attribute_value.lower())
                    if bool_result:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual attribute value are the same"
                    else:

                            expected_attribute_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_attribute_value)

                if bool_insert_kibana:

                                                      "The expected and actual attribute should be equal")

                                                                    actual_kibana_result,
                                                                    pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                    pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                    return bool_result
                else:
                    return bool_result
            except Exception as e:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The value of the attribute: " + attribute_name + " should be " + expected_attribute_value)
                str_actual_message = actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)
                str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
                self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message, str_actual_message,
                                                                pstr_error_code=str_error_code)

                return False

        def verify_text(self, plocator, expected_text_value, bool_insert_kibana=True, case_sensitive=False, **kwargs):
            """
            Description:
                |  This method accepts a locator or web element , fetches text from the web element ,
                |  compares it with the expected text value passed in parameters and based on the results returns True/False and
                |  also logs kibana results(optional) . The actual kibana result in this case is generated within the method.

            :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
            :type plocator: String/Web element
            :param expected_text_value: The expected text value of the web element
            :type expected_text_value: String
            :param case_sensitive: This parameter gives the option to user to compare the expected and actual text in a case sensitive manner
            :type case_sensitive: Boolean
            :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
            :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
            :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
            :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String

            :return: Boolean
            """
            actual_kibana_result = ""
            try:
                if 'explicit_wait' not in kwargs:
                    explicit_wait = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.default_explicit_wait
                else:
                    explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')
                bool_presence_result = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.is_element_present(plocator, explicit_wait)

                if bool_presence_result:
                    actual_text_value = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.get_web_element(plocator, explicit_wait).text
                    if case_sensitive:
                        bool_result = (expected_text_value == actual_text_value)
                        if bool_result:
                            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                        else:
                            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                                expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
                    else:
                        bool_result = (expected_text_value.lower() == actual_text_value.lower())
                        if bool_result:
                            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                        else:
                            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                                expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
                else:
                    bool_result = bool_presence_result
                    actual_kibana_result = "The given element was not found"

                if bool_insert_kibana:
                    str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                      "The expected and actual text should be equal")
                    str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
                    self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                                    actual_kibana_result,
                                                                    pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                    pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                    return bool_result
                else:
                    return bool_result
            except Exception as e:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The expected text value is " + expected_text_value)
                str_actual_message = actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)
                str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
                self.logger.exception(str_error_code)
                self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message, str_actual_message,
                                                                pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                return False

            Description:

    class Thick_Client:

        def __init__(self):
            self.assertions = Assertions()
            self.logger = self.assertions.logger

        def verify_element_is_visible(self, pobject_element, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
            """
            Description:
                |  This method defines the visibility of the element

            :param pobject_element: Element object for which need to check visibility
            :type pobject_element: Object
            :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
            :type bool_insert_kibana: boolean
            :param dynamic_wait: User can provide the wait for the element to get visible
            :type dynamic_wait: integer
               :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
            :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String
            :param pstr_actual_message(kwargs): User can use it to overwrite default actual message
            :type pstr_actual_message(kwargs): String
            :param pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_pass kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is True
            :type pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): String
            :param pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_fail kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is False
            :type pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): String


            :return: boolean
            Examples:
                |  verify_element_is_visible(quick_get_button,bool_insert_kibana=True)

            """

        def verify_element_value(self, pobject_element, pstr_validate_value, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
            """
            Description:
            |  This method is required to compare the value of the element with the expected value.

            :param pobject_element: Element object for which we need to find the value to compare
            :type pobject_element: Object
            :param pstr_validate_value: Expected value which is to be compare with the object output
            :type pstr_validate_value: String
            :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
            :type bool_insert_kibana: boolean

            :return: boolean
            Examples:
                |  verify_element_value(keyinst_text_box,"100369")

            """
            actual_kibana_result = ""
            str_error_code = None
            try:
                bool_result = False
                actual_value = PyGlobals().thick_client_actions.get_text_value(pobj_ele=pobject_element)

                if (actual_value == pstr_validate_value):
                    bool_result = True
                    actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                else:
                    actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + pstr_validate_value + ",Actual Value: " + actual_value + ""
                    bool_result = False
                    str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE

                if bool_insert_kibana:
                    if bool_result:
                        if 'pstr_expected_message' in kwargs:
                            PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message'),
                                                                  actual_kibana_result, "Pass")
                            return bool_result
                        else:
                            PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(
                                "The expected and actual text value are not same",
                                actual_kibana_result, "Pass")
                            return bool_result
                    else:
                        if 'pstr_expected_message' in kwargs:
                            PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message'),
                                                                  actual_kibana_result, "Fail",
                                                                  pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure=True,
                                                                  pstr_error=str_error_code)
                            return bool_result
                        else:
                            PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(
                                "The expected and actual text value are not same",
                                actual_kibana_result, "Fail", pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure=True,
                                pstr_error=str_error_code)
                            return bool_result
                else:
                    return bool_result
            except Exception as e:
                str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
                self.logger.exception(str_error_code)
                if 'pstr_expected_message' in kwargs:
                    PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message'),
                                                          actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(
                                                              e), "Fail", pstr_error=str_error_code)
                    return False
                else:
                    PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step("The expected text value is " + pstr_validate_value,
                                                          actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(
                                                              e), "Fail", pstr_error=str_error_code)
                    return False

    def verify_text(self, plocator, expected_text_value, bool_insert_kibana=True, case_sensitive=False, **kwargs):
        """
        Description:
            |  This method accepts a locator or web element , fetches text from the web element ,
            |  compares it with the expected text value passed in parameters and based on the results returns True/False and
            |  also logs kibana results(optional) . The actual kibana result in this case is generated within the method.

        :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
        :type plocator: String/Web element
        :param expected_text_value: The expected text value of the web element
        :type expected_text_value: String
        :param case_sensitive: This parameter gives the option to user to compare the expected and actual text in a case sensitive manner
        :type case_sensitive: Boolean
        :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
        :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
        :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
        :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String

        :return: Boolean
        """
        actual_kibana_result = ""
        try:
            if 'explicit_wait' not in kwargs:
                explicit_wait = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.default_explicit_wait
            else:
                explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')
            bool_presence_result = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.is_element_present(plocator, explicit_wait)

            if bool_presence_result:
                actual_text_value = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.get_web_element(plocator, explicit_wait).text
                if case_sensitive:
                    bool_result = (expected_text_value == actual_text_value)
                    if bool_result:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                    else:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                            expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
                else:
                    bool_result = (expected_text_value.lower() == actual_text_value.lower())
                    if bool_result:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                    else:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                            expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
            else:
                bool_result = bool_presence_result
                actual_kibana_result = "The given element was not found"

            if bool_insert_kibana:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The expected and actual text should be equal")
                str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
                self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                                actual_kibana_result,
                                                                pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                return bool_result
            else:
                return bool_result
        except Exception as e:
            str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                              "The expected text value is " + expected_text_value)
            str_actual_message = actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)
            str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
            self.logger.exception(str_error_code)
            self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message, str_actual_message,
                                                            pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
            return False

    def verify_attribute_value(self, plocator, attribute_name, expected_attribute_value, bool_insert_kibana=True,
                           case_sensitive=False, **kwargs):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method accepts a locator or web element , fetches value of attribute name from the web element ,
        |  compares it with the expected attribute value passed in parameters and based on the results returns True/False and
        |  also logs kibana results

    :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
    :type plocator: String/Web element
    :param attribute_name: The attribute name for which the value needs to be fetched
    :type attribute_name: String
    :param expected_attribute_value: The expected attribute value of the web element
    :type expected_attribute_value: String
    :param case_sensitive: This parameter gives the option to user to compare the expected and actual text in a case sensitive manner
    :type case_sensitive: Boolean
    :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
    :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
    :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
    :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String

    :return: Boolean
    """
    actual_kibana_result = ""
    try:
        if 'explicit_wait' not in kwargs:
            explicit_wait = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.default_explicit_wait
        else:
            explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')
        actual_attribute_value = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.get_attribute_value(plocator, attribute_name,
                                                                                       explicit_wait)

        if case_sensitive:
            bool_result = (expected_attribute_value == actual_attribute_value)
            if bool_result:
                actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual attribute value are the same"
            else:
                actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual attribute value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                    expected_attribute_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_attribute_value)
        else:
            bool_result = (expected_attribute_value.lower() == actual_attribute_value.lower())
            if bool_result:
                actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual attribute value are the same"
            else:
                actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual attribute value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                    expected_attribute_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_attribute_value)

        if bool_insert_kibana:
            str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                              "The expected and actual attribute should be equal")
            str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
            self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                            actual_kibana_result,
                                                            pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                            pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
            return bool_result
        else:
            return bool_result
    except Exception as e:
        str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                          "The value of the attribute: " + attribute_name + " should be " + expected_attribute_value)
        str_actual_message = actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)
        str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
        self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message, str_actual_message,
                                                        pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
        return False

    def verify_text(self, plocator, expected_text_value, bool_insert_kibana=True, case_sensitive=False, **kwargs):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method accepts a locator or web element , fetches text from the web element ,
        |  compares it with the expected text value passed in parameters and based on the results returns True/False and
        |  also logs kibana results(optional) . The actual kibana result in this case is generated within the method.

    :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
    :type plocator: String/Web element
    :param expected_text_value: The expected text value of the web element
    :type expected_text_value: String
    :param case_sensitive: This parameter gives the option to user to compare the expected and actual text in a case sensitive manner
    :type case_sensitive: Boolean
    :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
    :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
    :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
    :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String

    :return: Boolean
    """
    actual_kibana_result = ""
    try:
        if 'explicit_wait' not in kwargs:
            explicit_wait = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.default_explicit_wait
        else:
            explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')
        bool_presence_result = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.is_element_present(plocator, explicit_wait)

        if bool_presence_result:
            actual_text_value = PyGlobals().mobile_client_actions.get_web_element(plocator, explicit_wait).text
            if case_sensitive:
                bool_result = (expected_text_value == actual_text_value)
                if bool_result:
                    actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                else:
                    actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                        expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
            else:
                bool_result = (expected_text_value.lower() == actual_text_value.lower())
                if bool_result:
                    actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                else:
                    actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                        expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
        else:
            bool_result = bool_presence_result
            actual_kibana_result = "The given element was not found"

        if bool_insert_kibana:
            str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                              "The expected and actual text should be equal")
            str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
            self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                            actual_kibana_result,
                                                            pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                            pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
            return bool_result
        else:
            return bool_result
    except Exception as e:
        str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                          "The expected text value is " + expected_text_value)
        str_actual_message = actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)
        str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
        self.logger.exception(str_error_code)
        self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message, str_actual_message,
                                                        pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
        return False

    class Thick_Client:

    def __init__(self):
        self.assertions = Assertions()
        self.logger = self.assertions.logger

    def verify_element_is_visible(self, pobject_element, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
        """
        Description:
            |  This method defines the visibility of the element

        :param pobject_element: Element object for which need to check visibility
        :type pobject_element: Object
        :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
        :type bool_insert_kibana: boolean
        :param dynamic_wait: User can provide the wait for the element to get visible
        :type dynamic_wait: integer
           :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
        :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message(kwargs): User can use it to overwrite default actual message
        :type pstr_actual_message(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_pass kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is True
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_fail kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is False
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): String


        :return: boolean
        Examples:
            |  verify_element_is_visible(quick_get_button,bool_insert_kibana=True)

        """
        try:
            str_actual_message_on_pass = None
            str_actual_message_on_fail = None
            if 'dynamic_wait' not in kwargs:
                PyGlobals().thick_client_actions.dynamic_wait(pobject_element, 'visible')
            else:
                dynamic_wait = kwargs.get('dynamic_wait')
                PyGlobals().thick_client_actions.dynamic_wait(pobject_element, 'visible', dynamic_wait)

            bool_result = pobject_element.is_visible()
            if bool_insert_kibana:
                if bool_insert_kibana:
                    str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                      "The given element should be visible")
                    str_actual_message = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message')
                    if str_actual_message is None:
                        str_actual_message_on_pass = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_pass',
                                                                "The given element was visible.")
                        str_actual_message_on_fail = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_fail',
                                                                "The given element was not visible.")
                    str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
                    self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                                    str_actual_message,
                                                                    pstr_actual_message_on_pass=str_actual_message_on_pass,
                                                                    pstr_actual_message_on_fail=str_actual_message_on_fail,
                                                                    pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                    pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                    return bool_result
            else:
                return bool_result
        except Exception as e:
            str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                              "The given element should be visible on the page")
            str_actual_message = "The given element was not visible. The method threw an exception. " + str(e)
            str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
            self.logger.exception(str_error_code)
            self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message,
                                                            str_actual_message, pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
            return False

    def verify_element_is_enabled(self, pobject_element, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
        """
        Description:
            |  This method is to check the element is enabled.

        :param pobject_element: Element object for which need to check enabled
        :type pobject_element: Object
        :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
        :type bool_insert_kibana: boolean

        :return: Boolean

        """
        try:
            str_actual_message_on_pass = None
            str_actual_message_on_fail = None
            if 'dynamic_wait' not in kwargs:
                PyGlobals().thick_client_actions.dynamic_wait(pobject_element, 'enabled')

                dynamic_wait = kwargs.get('dynamic_wait')

            bool_result = pobject_element.is_enabled()
            if bool_insert_kibana:
                if bool_insert_kibana:
                    str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                      "The given element should be enabled")
                    str_actual_message = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message')

                        str_actual_message_on_pass = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_pass',

            else:
                return bool_result

        except Exception as e:
            str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                              "The given element should be enabled")
            str_actual_message = "The given element was not enabled. The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)
            str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
            self.logger.exception(str_error_code)
            self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message, str_actual_message)
            return False

    def verify_element_value(self, pobject_element, pstr_validate_value, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
        """
        Description:
        |  This method is required to compare the value of the element with the expected value.

        :param pobject_element: Element object for which we need to find the value to compare
        :type pobject_element: Object
        :param pstr_validate_value: Expected value which is to be compare with the object output
        :type pstr_validate_value: String
        :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
        :type bool_insert_kibana: boolean

        :return: boolean
        Examples:
            |  verify_element_value(keyinst_text_box,"100369")

        """
        actual_kibana_result = ""
        str_error_code = None
        try:
            bool_result = False
            actual_value = PyGlobals().thick_client_actions.get_text_value(pobj_ele=pobject_element)

            if (actual_value == pstr_validate_value):
                bool_result = True
                actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
            else:
                actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + pstr_validate_value + ",Actual Value: " + actual_value + ""
                bool_result = False
                str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE

            if bool_insert_kibana:
                if bool_result:
                    if 'pstr_expected_message' in kwargs:
                        PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message'),
                                                              actual_kibana_result, "Pass")
                        return bool_result
                    else:
                        PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(
                            "The expected and actual text value are not same",
                            actual_kibana_result, "Pass")
                        return bool_result
                else:
                    if 'pstr_expected_message' in kwargs:
                        PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message'),
                                                              actual_kibana_result, "Fail",
                                                              pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure=True,
                                                              pstr_error=str_error_code)
                        return bool_result
                    else:
                        PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(
                            "The expected and actual text value are not same",
                            actual_kibana_result, "Fail", pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure=True,
                            pstr_error=str_error_code)
                        return bool_result
            else:
                return bool_result
        except Exception as e:
            str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
            self.logger.exception(str_error_code)
            if 'pstr_expected_message' in kwargs:
                PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message'),
                                                      actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(
                                                          e), "Fail", pstr_error=str_error_code)
                return False
            else:
                PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step("The expected text value is " + pstr_validate_value,
                                                      actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(
                                                          e), "Fail", pstr_error=str_error_code)
                return False

    def verify_element_is_visible(self, pobject_element, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method defines the visibility of the element

    :param pobject_element: Element object for which need to check visibility
    :type pobject_element: Object
    :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
    :type bool_insert_kibana: boolean
    :param dynamic_wait: User can provide the wait for the element to get visible
    :type dynamic_wait: integer
       :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
    :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String
    :param pstr_actual_message(kwargs): User can use it to overwrite default actual message
    :type pstr_actual_message(kwargs): String
    :param pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_pass kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is True
    :type pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): String
    :param pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_fail kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is False
    :type pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): String


    :return: boolean
    Examples:
        |  verify_element_is_visible(quick_get_button,bool_insert_kibana=True)

    """
    try:
        str_actual_message_on_pass = None
        str_actual_message_on_fail = None
        if 'dynamic_wait' not in kwargs:
            PyGlobals().thick_client_actions.dynamic_wait(pobject_element, 'visible')
        else:
            dynamic_wait = kwargs.get('dynamic_wait')
            PyGlobals().thick_client_actions.dynamic_wait(pobject_element, 'visible', dynamic_wait)

        bool_result = pobject_element.is_visible()
        if bool_insert_kibana:
            if bool_insert_kibana:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The given element should be visible")
                str_actual_message = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message')
                if str_actual_message is None:
                    str_actual_message_on_pass = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_pass',
                                                            "The given element was visible.")
                    str_actual_message_on_fail = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_fail',
                                                            "The given element was not visible.")
                str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
                self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                                str_actual_message,
                                                                pstr_actual_message_on_pass=str_actual_message_on_pass,
                                                                pstr_actual_message_on_fail=str_actual_message_on_fail,
                                                                pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                return bool_result
        else:
            return bool_result
    except Exception as e:
        str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                          "The given element should be visible on the page")
        str_actual_message = "The given element was not visible. The method threw an exception. " + str(e)
        str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
        self.logger.exception(str_error_code)
        self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message,
                                                        str_actual_message, pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
        return False

    def verify_element_value(self, pobject_element, pstr_validate_value, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
    """
    Description:
    |  This method is required to compare the value of the element with the expected value.

    :param pobject_element: Element object for which we need to find the value to compare
    :type pobject_element: Object
    :param pstr_validate_value: Expected value which is to be compare with the object output
    :type pstr_validate_value: String
    :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
    :type bool_insert_kibana: boolean

    :return: boolean
    Examples:
        |  verify_element_value(keyinst_text_box,"100369")

    """
    actual_kibana_result = ""
    str_error_code = None
    try:
        bool_result = False
        actual_value = PyGlobals().thick_client_actions.get_text_value(pobj_ele=pobject_element)

        if (actual_value == pstr_validate_value):
            bool_result = True
            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
        else:
            actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + pstr_validate_value + ",Actual Value: " + actual_value + ""
            bool_result = False
            str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE

        if bool_insert_kibana:
            if bool_result:
                if 'pstr_expected_message' in kwargs:
                    PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message'),
                                                          actual_kibana_result, "Pass")
                    return bool_result
                else:
                    PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(
                        "The expected and actual text value are not same",
                        actual_kibana_result, "Pass")
                    return bool_result
            else:
                if 'pstr_expected_message' in kwargs:
                    PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message'),
                                                          actual_kibana_result, "Fail",
                                                          pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure=True,
                                                          pstr_error=str_error_code)
                    return bool_result
                else:
                    PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(
                        "The expected and actual text value are not same",
                        actual_kibana_result, "Fail", pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure=True,
                        pstr_error=str_error_code)
                    return bool_result
        else:
            return bool_result
    except Exception as e:
        str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
        self.logger.exception(str_error_code)
        if 'pstr_expected_message' in kwargs:
            PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step(kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message'),
                                                  actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(
                                                      e), "Fail", pstr_error=str_error_code)
            return False
        else:
            PyGlobals().kibana_report.insert_step("The expected text value is " + pstr_validate_value,
                                                  actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(
                                                      e), "Fail", pstr_error=str_error_code)
            return False

    class Web():

    error_utils = ErrorCategory()

    def __init__(self):
        self.assertions = Assertions()
        self.logger = self.assertions.logger

    def verify_element_is_visible(self, plocator, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
        """
        Description:
        	|  This method accepts a locator or web element and checks whether the element is visible on the page on not and based on the results returns True/False and also logs kibana results(optional)

        :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
        :type plocator: String/Web element
        :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
        :type bool_insert_kibana: Boolean
        :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
        :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
        :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
        :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message(kwargs): User can use it to overwrite default actual message
        :type pstr_actual_message(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_pass kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is True
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_fail kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is False
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): String

        :return: Boolean
        """
        try:
            str_actual_message_on_pass = None
            str_actual_message_on_fail = None
            if 'explicit_wait' not in kwargs:
                explicit_wait = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.default_explicit_wait
            else:
                explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')
            bool_result = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.is_element_displayed(plocator, explicit_wait)

            if bool_insert_kibana:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The given element/locator should be visible on the page")
                str_actual_message = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message')
                if str_actual_message is None:
                    str_actual_message_on_pass = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_pass',
                                                            "The given element/locator was visible.")
                    str_actual_message_on_fail = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_fail',
                                                            "The given element/locator was not visible.")

                str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
                self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                                str_actual_message,
                                                                pstr_actual_message_on_pass=str_actual_message_on_pass,
                                                                pstr_actual_message_on_fail=str_actual_message_on_fail,
                                                                pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                return bool_result
            else:
                return bool_result
        except Exception as e:
            str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                              "The given element/locator should be visible on the page")
            str_actual_message = "The given element/locator was not visible. The method threw an excepction. " + str(
                e)
            str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
            self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message,
                                                            str_actual_message, pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
            self.logger.exception(
                "The given element/locator was not visible. The method threw an excepction. " + str(e))
            return False

            return bool_result

            str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                              "The Expected value : " + pstr_expected_title + "should be equal to Actual Value :" + pstr_actual_page_title)
            str_actual_message = "The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)

                                                            pstr_error_code=str_error_code)

    def verify_element_is_present(self, plocator, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):

        :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
        :type bool_insert_kibana: Boolean
        :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
        :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
        :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
        :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message(kwargs): User can use it to overwrite default actual message
        :type pstr_actual_message(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_pass kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is True
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_fail kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is False
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): String

            str_actual_message_on_fail = None

            else:
                explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')

    def verify_page_url(self, pstr_expected_url, bool_insert_kibana=True, **kwargs):
        """
        Description:
            |  This method accepts a locator or web element and checks whether the element is present on the page on not and based on the results returns True/False and also logs kibana results(optional)

        :param pstr_expected_url: pstr_expected_url is expected URL
        :type pstr_expected_url: String
        :param bool_insert_kibana: This parameter gives the option to user to add kibana logs along with the verification or not
        :type bool_insert_kibana: Boolean
        :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
        :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
        :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
        :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message(kwargs): User can use it to overwrite default actual message
        :type pstr_actual_message(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_pass kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is True
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_pass(kwargs): String
        :param pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): pstr_actual_message_on_fail kwarg parameter is the actual message that would insert into kibana when a validation is False
        :type pstr_actual_message_on_fail(kwargs): String
        :return: Boolean
        """
        try:
            str_actual_message_on_pass = None
            str_actual_message_on_fail = None
            pstr_actual_url = ""
            pstr_actual_url = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.get_current_url()
            raise exceptions.ElementNotSelectableException
            bool_result = False
            if (pstr_actual_url == pstr_expected_url):
                bool_result = True
            if bool_insert_kibana:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The page URL should be as expected")
                str_actual_message = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message')

                    str_actual_message_on_pass = kwargs.get('pstr_actual_message_on_pass',
                                                            "Page URL is as expected. Expected : " + pstr_expected_url + "Actual : " + pstr_actual_url)

    def verify_text(self, plocator, expected_text_value, bool_insert_kibana=True, case_sensitive=False, **kwargs):
        """
        Description:
            |  This method accepts a locator or web element , fetches text from the web element ,
            |  compares it with the expected text value passed in parameters and based on the results returns True/False and
            |  also logs kibana results(optional) . The actual kibana result in this case is generated within the method.

        :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
        :type plocator: String/Web element
        :param expected_text_value: The expected text value of the web element
        :type expected_text_value: String
        :param case_sensitive: This parameter gives the option to user to compare the expected and actual text in a case sensitive manner
        :type case_sensitive: Boolean
        :param explicit_wait(kwargs): User can pass the explicit wait
        :type explicit_wait(kwargs): Integer
        :param pstr_expected_message(kwargs): This is the expected value/action that goes into the kibana logs
        :type pstr_expected_message(kwargs): String

        :return: Boolean
        """
        actual_kibana_result = ""
        try:
            if 'explicit_wait' not in kwargs:
                explicit_wait = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.default_explicit_wait
            else:
                explicit_wait = kwargs.get('explicit_wait')
            bool_presence_result = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.is_element_present(plocator, explicit_wait)

            if bool_presence_result:
                actual_text_value = PyGlobals().web_client_actions.get_web_element(plocator, explicit_wait).text
                if case_sensitive:
                    bool_result = (expected_text_value == actual_text_value)
                    if bool_result:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                    else:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                            expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
                else:
                    bool_result = (expected_text_value.lower() == actual_text_value.lower())
                    if bool_result:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are the same"
                    else:
                        actual_kibana_result = "The expected and actual text value are not the same, Expected Value: " + str(
                            expected_text_value) + " ,Actual Value: " + str(actual_text_value)
            else:
                bool_result = bool_presence_result
                actual_kibana_result = "The given element was not found"

            if bool_insert_kibana:
                str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                                  "The expected and actual text should be equal")
                str_error_code = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_THREE if not bool_result else None
                self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(bool_result, str_expected_message,
                                                                actual_kibana_result,
                                                                pbool_execute_after_failure=True,
                                                                pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
                return bool_result
            else:
                return bool_result
        except Exception as e:
            str_expected_message = kwargs.get('pstr_expected_message',
                                              "The expected text value is " + expected_text_value)
            str_actual_message = actual_kibana_result + " The method threw an excepction. " + str(e)
            str_error_code = self.error_utils.get_error_code_from_exception(e)
            self.assertions.kibana_insert_message_on_result(False, str_expected_message, str_actual_message,
                                                            pstr_error_code=str_error_code)
            return False

        """
        Description:
            |  This method accepts a locator or web element , fetches text from the web element ,

            |  also logs kibana results. The actual kibana result in this case is generated within the method.

        :param plocator: User can pass either the locator in the following format xpath=.//*[@id='123'] or pass the web element itself
